Reference

geometries

functions to create geometric objects parametrically or by sketching them

gs_point()

Create a point geom

gs_line()

Create a line geom

gs_polygon() gs_triangle() gs_square() gs_rectangle() gs_hexagon()

Create a polygon geom

gs_random()

Create a geom randomly

gs_tiles()

Create a regular tiling geom

gs_voronoi()

Create a voronoi tiling geom

transform geometry classes

functions that transform between geometric classes

gc_geom(<Spatial>) gc_geom(<sf>) gc_geom(<ppp>) gc_geom(<Raster>)

Transform a spatial object to class geom

gc_ppp(<geom>)

Transform a spatial object to class ppp

gc_raster(<geom>)

Transform a spatial object to class Raster*

gc_sf(<geom>)

Transform a spatial object to class sf

gc_sp(<geom>)

Transform a spatial object to class Spatial

getters and setters

methods that standardise dealing with geometric objects

getCRS(<ANY>) getCRS(<geom>) getCRS(<Spatial>) getCRS(<sf>) getCRS(<ppp>) getCRS(<Raster>)

Get the coordinate reference system of a spatial object.

getExtent(<ANY>) getExtent(<geom>) getExtent(<Spatial>) getExtent(<sf>) getExtent(<ppp>) getExtent(<Raster>) getExtent(<matrix>)

Get the extent (bounding box) of a spatial object.

getCols(<ANY>) getCols(<geom>) getCols(<Raster>) getCols(<matrix>)

Get the number of columns of a spatial object.

getRows(<ANY>) getRows(<geom>) getRows(<Raster>) getRows(<matrix>)

Get the number of rows of a spatial object.

getFeatures(<ANY>) getFeatures(<geom>) getFeatures(<Spatial>) getFeatures(<sf>) getFeatures(<ppp>) getFeatures(<Raster>) getFeatures(<matrix>)

Get the table of feature attributes

getGroups(<ANY>) getGroups(<geom>) getGroups(<Raster>) getGroups(<matrix>)

Get the table of group attributes

getHistory(<ANY>) getHistory(<geom>) getHistory(<Raster>)

Get the history of a spatial object.

getLayer(<ANY>) getLayer(<geom>) getLayer(<Spatial>) getLayer(<sf>) getLayer(<Raster>) getLayer(<matrix>)

Get a specific layer of a spatial object.

getPoints(<ANY>) getPoints(<geom>) getPoints(<Spatial>) getPoints(<sf>) getPoints(<ppp>) getPoints(<Raster>) getPoints(<matrix>)

Get the table of point attributes

getRes(<ANY>) getRes(<geom>) getRes(<Raster>) getRes(<matrix>)

Get the spatial resolution of a spatial object.

getType(<ANY>) getType(<geom>) getType(<Spatial>) getType(<sf>) getType(<ppp>) getType(<Raster>) getType(<matrix>)

Get the type of a spatial object.

getWindow(<ANY>) getWindow(<geom>) getWindow(<Spatial>) getWindow(<sf>) getWindow(<ppp>) getWindow(<Raster>) getWindow(<matrix>)

Get the reference window of a spatial object.

setCRS(<ANY>) setCRS(<geom>) setCRS(<Spatial>) setCRS(<sf>) setCRS(<Raster>)

Set (or transform) the coordinate reference system of a spatial object.

setFeatures(<ANY>) setFeatures(<geom>) setFeatures(<Spatial>) setFeatures(<sf>) setFeatures(<sfc>) setFeatures(<ppp>)

Set a table of feature attributes

setGroups(<ANY>) setGroups(<geom>) setGroups(<RasterLayer>)

Set a table of group attributes

setHistory(<ANY>) setHistory(<geom>) setHistory(<RasterLayer>)

Set additional entries to the history of an object

setWindow(<ANY>) setWindow(<geom>) setWindow(<ppp>)

Set the reference window of a spatial object.

standardised tools

functions that modify geometric objects of all supported classes

gt_rotate()

Rotate geometric objects

gt_reflect()

Reflect geometric objects

gt_scale()

Scale geometric objects

gt_sketch()

Sketch geoms

gt_skew()

Skew geometric objects

gt_stretch()

Stretch geometric objects

gt_translate()

Translate geometric objects

gt_subset()

Derive the subset of a geometric object

gt_locate()

Locate (and identify) clicks

visualise

plot geometric objects

visualise()

Visualise raster and geom objects

setTheme()

Create a new theme
